00:00:27.400 --> 00:00:30.770
PROFESSOR: So good afternoon.

00:00:30.770 --> 00:00:33.790
Our main topic today
is to understand

00:00:33.790 --> 00:00:38.040
light forces, in particular
the stimulated force using

00:00:38.040 --> 00:00:40.030
the dressed atom picture.

00:00:40.030 --> 00:00:44.690
And I hope once you understand
how light forces can

00:00:44.690 --> 00:00:46.680
be described in the
dressed atom picture

00:00:46.680 --> 00:00:49.010
you will love the
dressed atom picture,

00:00:49.010 --> 00:00:50.920
as most atomic physicists do.

00:00:50.920 --> 00:00:53.400
It is really the
language we use,

00:00:53.400 --> 00:00:57.110
the intuition we apply
to atomic systems.

00:00:57.110 --> 00:01:00.930
Whenever we have a laser
beam which drives the atom

00:01:00.930 --> 00:01:04.790
it is, in most situations,
more appropriate

00:01:04.790 --> 00:01:09.420
and better to use dressed
states as your basis states

00:01:09.420 --> 00:01:12.400
and not the naked,
the bare states, which

00:01:12.400 --> 00:01:15.010
are ground and excited state.

00:01:15.010 --> 00:01:17.620
Now I know last
week I quickly went

00:01:17.620 --> 00:01:19.370
though the dressed atom picture.

00:01:19.370 --> 00:01:24.520
Let me sort of go
through it in a fly-over

00:01:24.520 --> 00:01:26.890
by not doing any
of the derivation,

00:01:26.890 --> 00:01:29.440
but making a few
comments here and there.

00:01:29.440 --> 00:01:32.650
Also, because I want
that some of the results

00:01:32.650 --> 00:01:35.320
are fresh in your
head when we apply it

00:01:35.320 --> 00:01:38.220
to mechanical forces of light.

00:01:38.220 --> 00:01:43.460
So I told you that in
the dressed atom picture

00:01:43.460 --> 00:01:46.730
we have two kinds of
interactions, the atom

00:01:46.730 --> 00:01:49.460
interact with a vacuum,
with a reservoir

00:01:49.460 --> 00:01:53.120
of empty modes with
spontaneous emission.

00:01:53.120 --> 00:01:56.810
And we also interact
with a laser field.

00:01:56.810 --> 00:01:59.260
And the new feature about
the dressed atom picture

00:01:59.260 --> 00:02:02.495
is that we first
solve this exactly,

00:02:02.495 --> 00:02:06.360
we rediagonalize the Hamiltonian
for that Hilbert space,

00:02:06.360 --> 00:02:10.710
and then we allow spontaneous
emission to happen.

00:02:10.710 --> 00:02:15.940
Now the derivation is
pretty straightforward.

00:02:15.940 --> 00:02:21.690
After a number of
assumptions, we simply

00:02:21.690 --> 00:02:25.740
came to the two-by-two
matrix, where

00:02:25.740 --> 00:02:29.300
we have two levels of the
atoms coupled with the Rabi

00:02:29.300 --> 00:02:30.940
frequency.

00:02:30.940 --> 00:02:34.910
I derived it here for you using
the quantized electromagnetic

00:02:34.910 --> 00:02:35.900
field.

00:02:35.900 --> 00:02:40.380
But in your homework you derive
the same two-by-two matrix

00:02:40.380 --> 00:02:43.880
using a classical
electromagnetic field,

00:02:43.880 --> 00:02:45.610
which drives the atoms.

00:02:45.610 --> 00:02:49.430
And we've talked about the
similarities and differences

00:02:49.430 --> 00:02:50.070
last week.

00:02:52.499 --> 00:02:54.540
If you have any questions,
please raise your hand

00:02:54.540 --> 00:02:57.030
or interrupt me.

00:02:57.030 --> 00:02:59.940
Now two-by-two matrix
is fairly trivial.

00:02:59.940 --> 00:03:02.170
We can immediately
diagonalize it.

00:03:02.170 --> 00:03:04.630
And we find
Eigensolutions, which

00:03:04.630 --> 00:03:07.750
are just sine theta,
cosine theta, amplitude,

00:03:07.750 --> 00:03:10.530
linear superpositions
of the naked states.

00:03:10.530 --> 00:03:14.225
And the naked states are ground
and excited states, state A

00:03:14.225 --> 00:03:18.866
and state B, with N or N plus
1 photons in the laser field.

00:03:21.710 --> 00:03:23.100
So it's simple.

00:03:23.100 --> 00:03:25.215
It's just a two-by-two matrix.

00:03:25.215 --> 00:03:28.100
But the insight we
can get out of it

00:03:28.100 --> 00:03:30.960
is pretty profound
and pretty subtle.

00:03:30.960 --> 00:03:34.120
So what we first
discussed is-- and we

00:03:34.120 --> 00:03:37.140
will need that to
understand forces and energy

00:03:37.140 --> 00:03:41.970
conservation-- we can now
look at spontaneous emission.

00:03:41.970 --> 00:03:46.820
Spontaneous emission coupling
to the empty modes of the vacuum

00:03:46.820 --> 00:03:51.120
can only connect an excited
state B with a ground state A.

00:03:51.120 --> 00:03:53.940
And therefore, we
have diachromatically

00:03:53.940 --> 00:03:56.780
those four combinations,
represented here

00:03:56.780 --> 00:03:58.600
by those four arrows.

00:03:58.600 --> 00:04:01.510
And if you look for
the matrix element,

00:04:01.510 --> 00:04:05.430
you collect cosine theta
and sine theta factors.

00:04:05.430 --> 00:04:07.680
And that's what we did here.

00:04:07.680 --> 00:04:11.940
So we immediately get in
the dressed atom picture,

00:04:11.940 --> 00:04:14.860
an expression
which tells us what

00:04:14.860 --> 00:04:18.850
are the matrix elements for
the carrier, for the blue

00:04:18.850 --> 00:04:23.150
and for the red detuned
sideband of the Mollow triplet.

00:04:23.150 --> 00:04:25.870
But then there's
something else, and I

00:04:25.870 --> 00:04:28.630
edit this with the
lecture notes in green.

00:04:28.630 --> 00:04:32.190
We can also, now, if you know
what the transition rates are,

00:04:32.190 --> 00:04:35.550
we can set up rate equations
and can solve them.

00:04:35.550 --> 00:04:39.190
And once you solve a set of
differential equations for rate

00:04:39.190 --> 00:04:42.080
equations, you know what
the populations are.

00:04:42.080 --> 00:04:46.390
But now, today, I want to
tell you one more subtlety.

00:04:46.390 --> 00:04:50.800
You know already
that you cannot,

00:04:50.800 --> 00:04:54.270
in the most general situation,
formulate an equation with just

00:04:54.270 --> 00:04:55.660
a population.

00:04:55.660 --> 00:04:58.350
You know that we have
the master equation,

00:04:58.350 --> 00:05:00.240
we have the Optical
Bloch Equation.

00:05:00.240 --> 00:05:03.400
This is an equation
for the density matrix.

00:05:03.400 --> 00:05:07.070
And usually we get equations
where the populations

00:05:07.070 --> 00:05:09.020
are mixed with coherences.

00:05:09.020 --> 00:05:13.200
In other words, you cannot just
say the diagonal matrix element

00:05:13.200 --> 00:05:15.290
of the density matrix
is a population,

00:05:15.290 --> 00:05:19.460
and the change of population
is what goes out of this state

00:05:19.460 --> 00:05:21.260
and what arrives in this state.

00:05:21.260 --> 00:05:23.400
Coherences play a role.

00:05:23.400 --> 00:05:26.390
But, and this is what the
dressed atom picture does

00:05:26.390 --> 00:05:31.020
for you, in the limit that we
have a strong Rabi frequency--

00:05:31.020 --> 00:05:33.460
and this is the limit you
want to consider here--

00:05:33.460 --> 00:05:41.120
the matrix equation
decouples into an equation

00:05:41.120 --> 00:05:44.330
for populations and an
equation for coherences.

00:05:44.330 --> 00:05:47.650
And if something decouples
that should tell you we

00:05:47.650 --> 00:05:49.920
all on the right track, we
have the right description.

00:05:49.920 --> 00:05:52.970
In this description things
decouple, things are simpler.

00:05:52.970 --> 00:05:54.740
And that means
this description is

00:05:54.740 --> 00:05:59.510
most appropriate for the
physics we want to understand.

00:05:59.510 --> 00:06:03.060
Or, to say it more
specifically-- and all

00:06:03.060 --> 00:06:04.645
the details of course
are in the book

00:06:04.645 --> 00:06:08.110
Atom Photon Interaction-- you
can rewrite the Optical Bloch

00:06:08.110 --> 00:06:13.710
Equations not in the bare bases
but in the dressed atom basis.

00:06:13.710 --> 00:06:15.210
And in the dressed
atom basis you

00:06:15.210 --> 00:06:19.116
find this wonderful
separation between populations

00:06:19.116 --> 00:06:19.740
and coherences.

00:06:24.200 --> 00:06:27.820
So we have the simple
rate equations.

00:06:27.820 --> 00:06:29.740
By setting the
left hand side to 0

00:06:29.740 --> 00:06:32.810
we find the steady
state populations.

00:06:32.810 --> 00:06:36.160
This will be very important to
understand the light forces.

00:06:36.160 --> 00:06:40.680
But you should just remember
the steady state solution such

00:06:40.680 --> 00:06:41.620
as we know them.

00:06:41.620 --> 00:06:45.850
They're just exactly given
by this angle theta, which

00:06:45.850 --> 00:06:48.360
tells us what kind
of superposition

00:06:48.360 --> 00:06:51.800
of the bare states from
the dressed states.

00:06:51.800 --> 00:06:55.960
Remember in the case of
theta equals 45 degrees,

00:06:55.960 --> 00:07:01.640
the dressed states are just
symmetric and antisymmetric

00:07:01.640 --> 00:07:04.960
superposition of
the naked states.

00:07:04.960 --> 00:07:09.320
Now what is also important
is those rate equations,

00:07:09.320 --> 00:07:13.500
or those rate equations
have a time constant.

00:07:13.500 --> 00:07:18.280
The time constant is
here, the relaxation time

00:07:18.280 --> 00:07:19.740
for populations.

00:07:19.740 --> 00:07:22.020
And we know exactly what it is.

00:07:22.020 --> 00:07:24.260
It's a little bit more
complicated to find

00:07:24.260 --> 00:07:27.540
the equivalent equation
for the coherences.

00:07:27.540 --> 00:07:30.200
But just take my word,
the density matrix

00:07:30.200 --> 00:07:33.670
in the dressed atom basis
decouples into equation

00:07:33.670 --> 00:07:37.420
for population, which is
simple, equation for coherences,

00:07:37.420 --> 00:07:40.370
little bit harder to
derive but looks the same.

00:07:40.370 --> 00:07:44.950
And from this equation we have
now an expression for what

00:07:44.950 --> 00:07:47.810
is the relaxation
time for coherences.

00:07:47.810 --> 00:07:50.690
And just to show you
one non-trivial example,

00:07:50.690 --> 00:07:54.220
if you add up cosine square
plus sine square you get 1.

00:07:54.220 --> 00:07:56.130
But based on what
we derived we have

00:07:56.130 --> 00:07:59.440
to take cosine to the power
of 4, sine to the power of 4.

00:07:59.440 --> 00:08:03.650
And this gives us effect of
1/2, which will appear somewhere

00:08:03.650 --> 00:08:05.290
in an important place
in a few minutes.

00:08:10.190 --> 00:08:14.180
So with that we can now
address, we know now something

00:08:14.180 --> 00:08:17.300
about the intensities
of this Mollow triplet,

00:08:17.300 --> 00:08:21.872
because the intensity is nothing
else than the population,

00:08:21.872 --> 00:08:25.270
what is the population in
the initial state times

00:08:25.270 --> 00:08:28.070
the matrix element squared.

00:08:28.070 --> 00:08:31.190
But what is also-- what
comes out very naturally--

00:08:31.190 --> 00:08:34.340
is that we have
different widths.

00:08:34.340 --> 00:08:36.390
The features have
different widths.

00:08:36.390 --> 00:08:38.429
The sidebands have
a different width

00:08:38.429 --> 00:08:41.539
from the central part
of the Mollow triplet.

00:08:41.539 --> 00:08:44.732
And well, this is now
very naturally interpreted

00:08:44.732 --> 00:08:47.740
at one has a width,
which is a relaxation

00:08:47.740 --> 00:08:49.250
rate for the population.

00:08:49.250 --> 00:08:51.144
The other one, is the
sidebands have a width

00:08:51.144 --> 00:08:53.060
which is a relaxation
rate for the coherences.

00:08:58.370 --> 00:09:02.620
I showed you, and this was just
a reminder of a few weeks ago,

00:09:02.620 --> 00:09:06.350
that when we looked at the
linear matrix equation, which

00:09:06.350 --> 00:09:08.470
are the Optical
Bloch Equation, we

00:09:08.470 --> 00:09:11.820
discussed complex
eigenvalues mathematically.

00:09:11.820 --> 00:09:16.040
And those complex eigenvalues,
the imaginary part

00:09:16.040 --> 00:09:18.310
is the sideband frequency.

00:09:18.310 --> 00:09:21.730
And the real part
was the widths.

00:09:21.730 --> 00:09:24.750
What I have now, sort
of-- I can get everything

00:09:24.750 --> 00:09:26.100
from the dressed atom picture.

00:09:26.100 --> 00:09:29.430
But what I've gotten in a
very natural and simple way

00:09:29.430 --> 00:09:33.310
is this case, which is the
case where the dressed atom

00:09:33.310 --> 00:09:35.460
picture is particularly simple.

00:09:35.460 --> 00:09:37.550
It's called the
secular case, where

00:09:37.550 --> 00:09:40.700
the population and
coherences decouple.

00:09:40.700 --> 00:09:45.680
And so, what I just showed you,
that the population relaxation

00:09:45.680 --> 00:09:47.820
time is gamma over 2.

00:09:47.820 --> 00:09:55.550
This explains now
why, in this case,

00:09:55.550 --> 00:09:58.300
the widths of the
central feature

00:09:58.300 --> 00:10:03.940
is 1/2 of what it is
when we're on resonance.

00:10:03.940 --> 00:10:06.425
So everything is sort of
nicely playing out here.

00:10:10.390 --> 00:10:16.740
OK, any questions about
dressed level populations,

00:10:16.740 --> 00:10:22.670
rate equations,
the Mollow triplet?

00:10:22.670 --> 00:10:25.610
Because we want to apply
it now, in a few minutes,

00:10:25.610 --> 00:10:28.040
to the stimulated light force.

00:10:32.870 --> 00:10:35.810
But before I do
that, let me show you

00:10:35.810 --> 00:10:44.260
one nice piece of physics,
which can be formulated

00:10:44.260 --> 00:10:47.750
both in the bare,
in the uncoupled,

00:10:47.750 --> 00:10:50.280
and in the dressed state basis.

00:10:50.280 --> 00:10:53.350
And this is the process
of spontaneous emission.

00:10:53.350 --> 00:10:55.410
If an atom is in
the laser field,

00:10:55.410 --> 00:10:57.970
it just emits photon,
rapid fire photons.

00:10:57.970 --> 00:11:01.080
And I want to show you now,
how we would describe it

00:11:01.080 --> 00:11:03.370
in the bare basis,
how we describe it

00:11:03.370 --> 00:11:05.760
in the dressed basis.

00:11:05.760 --> 00:11:09.780
And we get two very different
physical pictures out of it.

00:11:09.780 --> 00:11:12.270
Well, in the bare
basis, maybe just

00:11:12.270 --> 00:11:14.150
think of quantum Monte
Carlo simulation,

00:11:14.150 --> 00:11:16.100
a photon has been
emitted, and that

00:11:16.100 --> 00:11:18.440
means we are in
the ground state.

00:11:18.440 --> 00:11:22.330
Now it takes a Rabi cycle
before the ground state

00:11:22.330 --> 00:11:24.700
atom is in the excited state.

00:11:24.700 --> 00:11:28.030
And when it is in the excited
state, it can emit again

00:11:28.030 --> 00:11:29.820
and goes back to
the ground state.

00:11:29.820 --> 00:11:32.220
And then things start over.

00:11:32.220 --> 00:11:37.300
So the picture you obtain here
is the picture of antibunching,

00:11:37.300 --> 00:11:40.560
that the atom emits
a photon, but then it

00:11:40.560 --> 00:11:44.840
takes the inverse Rabi
frequency to load the gun again.

00:11:44.840 --> 00:11:47.910
And then it can fire again
and emit the next photon.

00:11:47.910 --> 00:11:52.610
So therefore, the probability
of getting another photon right

00:11:52.610 --> 00:11:57.280
after you've observed the
first photon is reduced,

00:11:57.280 --> 00:12:00.040
or T equals 0, it is exactly 0.

00:12:00.040 --> 00:12:02.490
And this is antibunching,
the photons are antibunched.

00:12:05.140 --> 00:12:09.450
So this is how we would describe
the radiative cascade, how

00:12:09.450 --> 00:12:13.200
we go from N to N minus 1, to
N minus 2, how we lose photons

00:12:13.200 --> 00:12:15.430
from the laser
field and dump them

00:12:15.430 --> 00:12:18.200
into the empty
modes of the vacuum.

00:12:18.200 --> 00:12:22.560
That's how we describe it
in the uncoupled basis.

00:12:22.560 --> 00:12:25.143
Well in the dressed
basis we have sort of

00:12:25.143 --> 00:12:29.800
diagonalized the
atoms interacting

00:12:29.800 --> 00:12:31.460
with the strong laser field.

00:12:31.460 --> 00:12:34.350
And now we would have
the following picture.

00:12:34.350 --> 00:12:36.630
We have this manifold here.

00:12:36.630 --> 00:12:38.700
We can emit from this manifold.

00:12:38.700 --> 00:12:41.800
And we can go to the upper
or lower dressed state.

00:12:41.800 --> 00:12:45.010
And then, the next
thing will happen again.

00:12:45.010 --> 00:12:48.770
But what we realize here, if we
are in the upper dressed state,

00:12:48.770 --> 00:12:51.420
we can either emit
on the carrier

00:12:51.420 --> 00:12:53.970
or we can emit a
blue detune sideband.

00:12:53.970 --> 00:12:57.890
But once we have emitted
a blue detune sideband,

00:12:57.890 --> 00:13:01.550
the next sideband has to be
red detuned because we are now

00:13:01.550 --> 00:13:06.240
in the lower dressed state,
and we need a lower sideband

00:13:06.240 --> 00:13:08.710
to go back to the
upper dressed state.

00:13:08.710 --> 00:13:13.630
So what this picture gives
us, it gives us the sidebands

00:13:13.630 --> 00:13:16.550
because we are resolving the
splitting in this picture.

00:13:16.550 --> 00:13:19.360
And secondly, it
tells us that there

00:13:19.360 --> 00:13:22.980
is an alternation between
the blue detuned photons

00:13:22.980 --> 00:13:24.306
and the red detuned photon.

00:13:29.270 --> 00:13:32.880
Now you would say, well
aren't those two pictures

00:13:32.880 --> 00:13:33.940
really different?

00:13:33.940 --> 00:13:35.940
In one case we
have antibunching,

00:13:35.940 --> 00:13:37.920
and all of the
photons are the same.

00:13:37.920 --> 00:13:40.720
And over here I talk
about an alternation

00:13:40.720 --> 00:13:43.640
between the blue and
the red sideband.

00:13:43.640 --> 00:13:48.060
Well again, the two
pictures are complementary.

00:13:48.060 --> 00:13:51.870
In this case, if I want to
resolve the antibunching

00:13:51.870 --> 00:13:53.940
I need a temporal
resolution which

00:13:53.940 --> 00:13:57.130
is better than the
inverse Rabi frequency.

00:13:57.130 --> 00:14:01.430
But if my temporal resolution
is better than the inverse Rabi

00:14:01.430 --> 00:14:05.740
frequency then I don't have
the spectral resolution

00:14:05.740 --> 00:14:09.180
to observe the sidebands,
and vice versa.

00:14:09.180 --> 00:14:11.070
If I want to resolve
the sidebands,

00:14:11.070 --> 00:14:15.990
if I want to distinguish the red
from the blue detuned sideband

00:14:15.990 --> 00:14:19.470
of the Mollow triplet I
cannot run the experiment with

00:14:19.470 --> 00:14:22.880
the spectral resolution, which
would be required to observe

00:14:22.880 --> 00:14:25.120
the antibunching.

00:14:25.120 --> 00:14:27.370
So these are sort of
two different pictures.

00:14:27.370 --> 00:14:29.890
One is sort of in terms
of energy eigenstates

00:14:29.890 --> 00:14:31.670
when we have
spectral resolution.

00:14:31.670 --> 00:14:34.210
And this other picture
is more appropriate

00:14:34.210 --> 00:14:37.810
when we're interested in
the short time domain.

00:14:37.810 --> 00:14:39.310
So in that sense, you need both.

00:14:39.310 --> 00:14:41.040
You need the bare basis.

00:14:41.040 --> 00:14:42.760
You need to dressed basis.

00:14:42.760 --> 00:14:47.530
And you have to just know for
which physical process, which

00:14:47.530 --> 00:14:52.013
of them allows the more
direct description.

00:14:52.013 --> 00:14:52.513
Questions?

00:15:00.640 --> 00:15:07.730
OK, so this was partly
review, partly preparation

00:15:07.730 --> 00:15:10.390
for the next big
chapter, namely we

00:15:10.390 --> 00:15:13.520
want to understand the dipole
forces within the dressed atom

00:15:13.520 --> 00:15:14.990
picture.

00:15:14.990 --> 00:15:19.670
The book Atom Photon Interaction
has a nice summary of it.

00:15:19.670 --> 00:15:23.640
But the more detailed picture,
and I heavily draw from this,

00:15:23.640 --> 00:15:27.450
is in the truly seminal article
by Jean Dalibard and Claude

00:15:27.450 --> 00:15:28.890
Cohen-Tannoudji.

00:15:28.890 --> 00:15:33.280
I've linked this
article to our website.

00:15:33.280 --> 00:15:45.000
So I've summarized here pretty
much what I just told you.

00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:48.960
This is sort of the summary
from the previous section.

00:15:48.960 --> 00:15:52.040
What we have to know is
to understand light forces

00:15:52.040 --> 00:15:54.650
in the dressed atom
picture is number one,

00:15:54.650 --> 00:15:57.191
the energy speaking
between the two.

00:15:57.191 --> 00:16:03.170
The splitting between the two is
the generalized Rabi frequency.

00:16:03.170 --> 00:16:05.950
If there's anything
which is not--

00:16:05.950 --> 00:16:09.130
well I shouldn't say 100%--
but at least 90% clear to you,

00:16:09.130 --> 00:16:10.310
ask me question.

00:16:10.310 --> 00:16:12.130
I mean these are the
results we really

00:16:12.130 --> 00:16:14.180
need for the
following discussion.

00:16:14.180 --> 00:16:16.200
So number one is
the dressed energy

00:16:16.200 --> 00:16:20.680
levels are split by the
generalized Rabi frequency.

00:16:20.680 --> 00:16:26.306
Number two is with
this angle theta, which

00:16:26.306 --> 00:16:27.930
came from the solution
of diagonalizing

00:16:27.930 --> 00:16:31.400
the two-by-two matrix, we
have now the steady state

00:16:31.400 --> 00:16:35.930
populations in the upper and
in the lower dressed state.

00:16:35.930 --> 00:16:40.970
And the third thing is when
we have a population when

00:16:40.970 --> 00:16:46.060
we are not in steady state, then
the steady state populations

00:16:46.060 --> 00:16:50.680
are obtained with the time
constant, which is given here.

00:16:50.680 --> 00:16:54.710
The time constant
is not just gamma,

00:16:54.710 --> 00:16:59.630
it's gamma times these
trigonometric functions.

00:16:59.630 --> 00:17:01.570
So these are simple ingredients.

00:17:01.570 --> 00:17:03.910
But by using those
ingredients we

00:17:03.910 --> 00:17:11.450
can get a very nice formulation
for the stimulated force.

00:17:19.819 --> 00:17:22.140
So what I've shown
here is, and this

00:17:22.140 --> 00:17:30.380
is the situation we want
to focus on for a while.

00:17:30.380 --> 00:17:34.070
Assume you focus a laser beam.

00:17:34.070 --> 00:17:38.290
Then plot it as a
function of position.

00:17:38.290 --> 00:17:40.590
The atom is outside
the laser beam,

00:17:40.590 --> 00:17:42.495
it goes into the
laser beam where

00:17:42.495 --> 00:17:45.560
it experiences the
electromagnetic field.

00:17:45.560 --> 00:17:48.320
And if it goes further it
has crossed the laser beam

00:17:48.320 --> 00:17:52.080
and is out of the
laser beam again.

00:17:52.080 --> 00:17:56.800
So what happens is the splitting
between the two dressed

00:17:56.800 --> 00:18:00.380
energy levels is the
generalized Rabi frequency.

00:18:00.380 --> 00:18:04.150
And this is outside the laser
beam, simply the detuning.

00:18:04.150 --> 00:18:06.520
But then when the
laser beam is on,

00:18:06.520 --> 00:18:08.746
the generalized Rabi
frequency gets larger.

00:18:08.746 --> 00:18:11.120
We have a larger lar splitting
between the dressed energy

00:18:11.120 --> 00:18:14.160
levels, and so on.

00:18:14.160 --> 00:18:18.100
What is also important
is that if the laser is

00:18:18.100 --> 00:18:24.510
red detuned, which is here, the
lower dressed level correlates,

00:18:24.510 --> 00:18:26.750
corresponds to the ground state.

00:18:26.750 --> 00:18:38.180
Whereas for blue detuning the
ground state in this limit,

00:18:38.180 --> 00:18:41.380
the ground state correlates
with the upper dressed level.

00:18:41.380 --> 00:18:42.830
So it's important.

00:18:42.830 --> 00:18:46.920
So therefore an atom in this
situation-- because atoms

00:18:46.920 --> 00:18:48.430
are always more in
the ground state

00:18:48.430 --> 00:18:50.280
than in the excited
state-- an atom

00:18:50.280 --> 00:18:52.849
will have more population
in the upper dressed level.

00:18:52.849 --> 00:18:55.140
And here it will have more
population the lower dressed

00:18:55.140 --> 00:18:55.640
level.

00:18:58.720 --> 00:19:01.050
So what we want to
do now is we want

00:19:01.050 --> 00:19:06.830
to rewrite the stimulated light
force, or the dipole force,

00:19:06.830 --> 00:19:11.770
as we want to express it
through the forces acting

00:19:11.770 --> 00:19:13.800
on the dressed atom level.

00:19:13.800 --> 00:19:19.080
Well, I told you that we have a
splitting of the dressed energy

00:19:19.080 --> 00:19:21.640
levels by the generalized
Rabi frequency.

00:19:21.640 --> 00:19:24.735
So therefore, if
I just cover that,

00:19:24.735 --> 00:19:28.172
the energy level
of the two dressed

00:19:28.172 --> 00:19:32.630
levels is h bar over 2 plus
minus the generalized Rabi

00:19:32.630 --> 00:19:33.760
frequency.

00:19:33.760 --> 00:19:37.590
And the force if an atom is
in one of the dressed levels

00:19:37.590 --> 00:19:39.720
is simply the gradient of that.

00:19:39.720 --> 00:19:43.000
So therefore we have the picture
that the two dressed energy

00:19:43.000 --> 00:19:45.540
levels, atoms in those
two dressed levels,

00:19:45.540 --> 00:19:48.360
always experience
opposite forces.

00:19:51.080 --> 00:19:54.453
Then an expression
for the net force

00:19:54.453 --> 00:19:58.130
is that the average
dipole force is

00:19:58.130 --> 00:20:00.830
the force in dressed
level one times

00:20:00.830 --> 00:20:03.660
the probability that the
atom is in dressed level one.

00:20:03.660 --> 00:20:05.670
And the same for two.

00:20:05.670 --> 00:20:09.270
And if you sum it up we
get exactly the expression

00:20:09.270 --> 00:20:13.910
we have derived earlier for
the stimulated light force.

00:20:13.910 --> 00:20:18.080
But let's just sort of look at
it in the following picture.

00:20:18.080 --> 00:20:22.320
If we are blue detuned,
and let's assume

00:20:22.320 --> 00:20:24.230
we are not saturating
the transition,

00:20:24.230 --> 00:20:27.670
so therefore the atom will be
mainly in the ground state.

00:20:27.670 --> 00:20:31.790
So you have more
population in that state.

00:20:31.790 --> 00:20:35.910
But, well, if the
laser power is 0,

00:20:35.910 --> 00:20:37.890
we have 100% population here.

00:20:37.890 --> 00:20:40.400
But when the atom moves
into the laser beam

00:20:40.400 --> 00:20:44.130
there is a superposition of
ground and excited state.

00:20:44.130 --> 00:20:46.440
But that also means
there's a superposition

00:20:46.440 --> 00:20:49.420
of upper and lower
dressed level.

00:20:49.420 --> 00:20:52.320
But we have always, of
course, more population

00:20:52.320 --> 00:20:55.300
in the dressed level which
connects to the ground state

00:20:55.300 --> 00:21:02.140
because an atom will-- well, it
also comes out of the solution.

00:21:02.140 --> 00:21:07.350
But it's natural, just assume
you make the laser beam weak,

00:21:07.350 --> 00:21:09.440
you start in the ground
state and everything

00:21:09.440 --> 00:21:10.929
is sort of connected.

00:21:10.929 --> 00:21:12.345
The ground state
is simply dressed

00:21:12.345 --> 00:21:16.630
by a small excited
state contribution.

00:21:16.630 --> 00:21:20.850
So that explains it, why
for blue detuned light,

00:21:20.850 --> 00:21:23.380
the physics is mainly in
the upper dressed level.

00:21:23.380 --> 00:21:27.590
And we see the repulsive dipole
force of a blue detuned laser.

00:21:27.590 --> 00:21:30.850
Whereas, for red detuned
light, the dominant population

00:21:30.850 --> 00:21:33.180
is in the lower
dressed level, and we

00:21:33.180 --> 00:21:36.560
have an attractive force.

00:21:36.560 --> 00:21:38.080
Well that's simple.

00:21:41.638 --> 00:21:46.420
We haven't gained so
much, but you'll see,

00:21:46.420 --> 00:21:50.560
we can now rapidly gain insight
by take it to the next level.

00:21:50.560 --> 00:21:53.690
Let me first mention
a trivial example.

00:21:53.690 --> 00:21:56.390
And this is when we
are on resonance.

00:21:56.390 --> 00:22:00.410
When we are on resonance we
have equal population in the two

00:22:00.410 --> 00:22:04.190
dressed states, they
are resonantly mixed.

00:22:04.190 --> 00:22:06.846
And therefore if the
population in the two

00:22:06.846 --> 00:22:10.370
dressed states is the same,
but the atoms experience

00:22:10.370 --> 00:22:14.220
opposite forces, that means the
dipole force average out to 0.

00:22:17.342 --> 00:22:21.970
In a few minutes I want
to calculate for you

00:22:21.970 --> 00:22:24.630
what the heating is.

00:22:24.630 --> 00:22:26.810
The dipole force is 0.

00:22:26.810 --> 00:22:31.180
But you know the atom in
this radiative cascade

00:22:31.180 --> 00:22:35.500
is making transitions between
upper and lower dressed level.

00:22:35.500 --> 00:22:37.670
So what does it
mean for the atom?

00:22:37.670 --> 00:22:41.100
When it is in one dressed
level it experience the force

00:22:41.100 --> 00:22:42.160
from this side.

00:22:42.160 --> 00:22:44.300
If the atom is in the
other dressed level,

00:22:44.300 --> 00:22:47.290
it's experience a
force from that side.

00:22:47.290 --> 00:22:53.350
So the atom is actually subject
to an average force which is 0.

00:22:53.350 --> 00:22:56.570
But if you take these picture
literally, and you can,

00:22:56.570 --> 00:22:59.600
the atom is really whacked
left, right, left, right, left,

00:22:59.600 --> 00:23:00.100
right.

00:23:00.100 --> 00:23:01.950
And there is fluctuations.

00:23:01.950 --> 00:23:05.930
And we can use those fluctuating
forces to immediately calculate

00:23:05.930 --> 00:23:07.250
what is the heating.

00:23:07.250 --> 00:23:11.410
The force average is 0, but
the fluctuations of the force

00:23:11.410 --> 00:23:12.990
cause heating.

00:23:12.990 --> 00:23:16.430
So that's immediately the
next step of physical insight

00:23:16.430 --> 00:23:19.120
we will get out of this picture.

00:23:19.120 --> 00:23:22.490
But before I do that I
want to do something else.

00:23:22.490 --> 00:23:29.730
I want to discuss
what happens now

00:23:29.730 --> 00:23:34.010
to the force when the
atom is slowly moving.

00:23:34.010 --> 00:23:41.440
Remember, there is
still one phenomenon

00:23:41.440 --> 00:23:43.630
which I owe you an
explanation for.

00:23:43.630 --> 00:23:46.480
And this is when we
discussed molasses.

00:23:46.480 --> 00:23:48.960
We always had the effect
in optical molasses

00:23:48.960 --> 00:23:51.000
with a spontaneous
light force that we

00:23:51.000 --> 00:23:55.330
need red detuning of the
laser beam to get cooling.

00:23:55.330 --> 00:23:58.280
The simple picture is the atom
absorbs a red detuned photon

00:23:58.280 --> 00:24:00.870
and emits away a
resonant photon.

00:24:00.870 --> 00:24:03.460
And then that energy
difference is taken away

00:24:03.460 --> 00:24:06.260
from the kinetic energy,
and this is cooling.

00:24:06.260 --> 00:24:08.680
But then I told
you that when you

00:24:08.680 --> 00:24:12.690
go to higher power
of the standing wave,

00:24:12.690 --> 00:24:17.330
the sine of alpha of the
friction coefficient reverses.

00:24:17.330 --> 00:24:20.950
And that means cooling is now
done by blue detuned light,

00:24:20.950 --> 00:24:23.287
heating is done by
red detuned light.

00:24:23.287 --> 00:24:24.870
And that's what we
want to understand.

00:24:29.530 --> 00:24:35.090
So in order to get any cooling
effect, or heating effect,

00:24:35.090 --> 00:24:39.450
we have to now
change the equation

00:24:39.450 --> 00:24:41.890
we had for the
average dipole force.

00:24:41.890 --> 00:24:44.690
Remember also, the
average dipole force,

00:24:44.690 --> 00:24:47.575
we did that earlier, can be
derived from a potential.

00:24:47.575 --> 00:24:49.620
It's a gradient over potential.

00:24:49.620 --> 00:24:52.180
So therefore, when you
fly through a laser beam

00:24:52.180 --> 00:24:55.230
you go down and up or up
and down the potential,

00:24:55.230 --> 00:24:57.560
but nothing has happened to you.

00:24:57.560 --> 00:25:00.310
But the assumption
we had for that

00:25:00.310 --> 00:25:05.810
is that the dipole force was
calculated with a steady state

00:25:05.810 --> 00:25:07.500
population.

00:25:07.500 --> 00:25:10.860
So now we want to say
if the atom is slowly

00:25:10.860 --> 00:25:15.410
moving it may not
be fully adiabatic,

00:25:15.410 --> 00:25:18.120
and we want to calculate
the first correction

00:25:18.120 --> 00:25:21.150
to the non-adiabaticity.

00:25:21.150 --> 00:25:24.310
So in other words, we have
the following picture.

00:25:24.310 --> 00:25:26.950
When an atom flies
through the laser beam

00:25:26.950 --> 00:25:32.210
it needs a certain time
to adjust its population.

00:25:32.210 --> 00:25:35.230
And the question,
what is this time?

00:25:35.230 --> 00:25:38.870
Well, it is the relaxation
time for the populations

00:25:38.870 --> 00:25:40.990
among the dressed
states to adjust.

00:25:40.990 --> 00:25:44.400
And this is exactly the
inverse of the rate gamma

00:25:44.400 --> 00:25:46.575
pop, which we have
calculated earlier.

00:25:51.590 --> 00:25:56.190
So the physical picture now
is that in the dressed level

00:25:56.190 --> 00:26:00.250
one and two, the population
at any given moment

00:26:00.250 --> 00:26:03.970
is almost the steady state.

00:26:03.970 --> 00:26:06.990
But there is a time
lag, a time lag

00:26:06.990 --> 00:26:09.960
by the time it takes to relax.

00:26:09.960 --> 00:26:12.160
So in other words, the
atom is always a little bit

00:26:12.160 --> 00:26:15.140
behind in adjusting
to the laser field

00:26:15.140 --> 00:26:19.190
because it takes a
finite amount of time.

00:26:19.190 --> 00:26:25.190
So let's now try to understand,
in this picture which

00:26:25.190 --> 00:26:27.980
we have obtained
with a laser beam

00:26:27.980 --> 00:26:33.450
the two dressed levels and
the atom flying through,

00:26:33.450 --> 00:26:41.900
let's try to understand what
this extra lag time means.

00:26:41.900 --> 00:26:46.170
So the atom is flying
into the laser beam.

00:26:46.170 --> 00:26:48.620
It starts out in
the ground state,

00:26:48.620 --> 00:26:53.330
which means 100% in the
upper dressed energy level.

00:26:53.330 --> 00:26:57.100
Now, in the laser beam the
higher the laser power is,

00:26:57.100 --> 00:27:01.980
the more there is a mixture of
the other dressed energy level.

00:27:01.980 --> 00:27:04.870
But what happens is,
when the atom is here,

00:27:04.870 --> 00:27:09.530
when it just assume it flies in,
and there was not enough time

00:27:09.530 --> 00:27:12.330
to adjust the
population, that would

00:27:12.330 --> 00:27:16.190
mean that the atom-- and this
is indicated with the red dots--

00:27:16.190 --> 00:27:18.450
that the atom has a
little bit of more

00:27:18.450 --> 00:27:20.680
population in the
upper dressed level

00:27:20.680 --> 00:27:23.450
than it would have
in equilibrium

00:27:23.450 --> 00:27:25.290
But what does it
mean for the force

00:27:25.290 --> 00:27:29.570
now, if there is more
population here than there?

00:27:29.570 --> 00:27:33.120
Well, the more population
you have in the upper state,

00:27:33.120 --> 00:27:35.030
the more you're
climbing up a hill,

00:27:35.030 --> 00:27:37.320
the more you get a
force to the left.

00:27:37.320 --> 00:27:41.560
So this red arrow shows due
to the non-adiabaticity,

00:27:41.560 --> 00:27:44.410
due to the time lag, there
is a little extra force

00:27:44.410 --> 00:27:47.390
to the left hand side.

00:27:47.390 --> 00:27:49.710
So this is on the up hill.

00:27:49.710 --> 00:27:52.810
Let's now understand what
happens on the down hill.

00:27:52.810 --> 00:27:54.980
Well, we just have to
keep track of signs.

00:27:54.980 --> 00:27:59.630
Here, the atom, in a
fairly high laser field,

00:27:59.630 --> 00:28:02.620
is in the upper dressed level
with a mixture in the lower

00:28:02.620 --> 00:28:03.580
dressed level.

00:28:03.580 --> 00:28:07.040
But now it flies out
of the laser beam,

00:28:07.040 --> 00:28:10.490
but it cannot immediately
adjust its population.

00:28:10.490 --> 00:28:14.160
And that means it
wants to have now

00:28:14.160 --> 00:28:17.280
more population in the
upper dressed level

00:28:17.280 --> 00:28:19.250
but it hasn't fully adjusted.

00:28:19.250 --> 00:28:23.700
So therefore, instead of
having the blue bullet, which

00:28:23.700 --> 00:28:27.270
represents equilibrium, the
atom has the red bullet.

00:28:27.270 --> 00:28:30.440
It has a little bit
lower population in that,

00:28:30.440 --> 00:28:32.940
and higher population there.

00:28:32.940 --> 00:28:36.430
But lower population here
and hire population here

00:28:36.430 --> 00:28:39.660
means-- if you have a little
bit higher population than you

00:28:39.660 --> 00:28:43.500
should have here it means
you are climbing up the hill,

00:28:43.500 --> 00:28:49.040
and there is an extra force,
which is again, to the left.

00:28:49.040 --> 00:28:53.690
So we realize the
n the time lag,

00:28:53.690 --> 00:28:57.860
means when an atom goes up
the hill there's a little bit

00:28:57.860 --> 00:28:59.180
extra force to the left.

00:28:59.180 --> 00:29:00.720
And when it goes
down the hill there

00:29:00.720 --> 00:29:03.080
is a little bit extra
force to the left.

00:29:03.080 --> 00:29:07.300
And after it has flown
through the steady state

00:29:07.300 --> 00:29:10.410
part of the force roller
coaster up down, which

00:29:10.410 --> 00:29:14.110
can be derived from a
potential, has integrated to 0.

00:29:14.110 --> 00:29:17.530
But what is left is this
non-adiabatic component

00:29:17.530 --> 00:29:22.340
of the force which is
slowing down the atom.

00:29:22.340 --> 00:29:28.750
In other words, I have shown
you in this simple picture

00:29:28.750 --> 00:29:34.370
that the time lag in adjusting
the dressed energy population

00:29:34.370 --> 00:29:39.370
means that there is a small
differential force which

00:29:39.370 --> 00:29:41.860
is slowing down the atom.

00:29:41.860 --> 00:29:45.460
And what I assumed
here was blue detuning.

00:29:45.460 --> 00:29:50.820
So we have cooling, we have
friction for blue detuned light

00:29:50.820 --> 00:29:52.515
when it comes to the
stimulated force.

00:29:56.190 --> 00:30:02.710
Now this picture, this
equation that the population is

00:30:02.710 --> 00:30:07.080
a steady state at the
given position minus a time

00:30:07.080 --> 00:30:11.880
lag, we can solve it.

00:30:11.880 --> 00:30:13.820
And I'm not doing
it here because it

00:30:13.820 --> 00:30:15.920
involves a few
mathematical equations.

00:30:15.920 --> 00:30:19.160
But by just using these answers,
and the rest is straight

00:30:19.160 --> 00:30:23.030
forward, you can then
arrive at an expression

00:30:23.030 --> 00:30:26.330
for the stimulated
for the dipole force.

