00:39:18.580 --> 00:39:21.890
or momentum is the
integral of force.

00:39:21.890 --> 00:39:26.550
So we can exactly rewrite that
momentum diffusion coefficient

00:39:26.550 --> 00:39:31.480
by an integral over
correlation function of forces.

00:39:31.480 --> 00:39:34.430
And then we have the
nice physical picture

00:39:34.430 --> 00:39:37.410
that with increase
of kinetic energy,

00:39:37.410 --> 00:39:39.420
the momentum
diffusion coefficient

00:39:39.420 --> 00:39:42.871
comes because we have
fluctuations of the force.

