00:44:36.470 --> 00:44:40.860
And then we multiply with the
spontaneous emission rate,

00:44:40.860 --> 00:44:45.620
which for resonance
system is gamma over 2.

00:44:45.620 --> 00:44:49.830
And with that we get now
the heating coefficient,

00:44:49.830 --> 00:44:54.910
the momentum
diffusion coefficient

00:44:54.910 --> 00:44:58.280
for an atom which is
exposed to resonant light

00:44:58.280 --> 00:44:59.800
due to the stimulated
light force.

